  "title": "Executive/Senior Executive (Volunteer Centre) (Jurong East)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities: -</strong></p><ul><li>Support the management and delivery of SG Cares programme-funded initiatives, ensuring all key performance indicators (KPIs) are met. </li><li>Oversee operational risk, quality assurance, and compliance to maintain the integrity and impact of volunteer-led programmes.</li><li>Build and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders, including community partners and volunteers, using various engagement platforms. </li><li>Lead the planning and execution of volunteer recognition and engagement activities to foster a positive, motivated volunteer base.</li><li>Assess and plan for the charity’s volunteer manpower needs, identifying required skills and competencies. </li><li>Ensure volunteers are equipped with the necessary training and resources to fulfil their roles effectively.</li><li>Identify and cultivate potential sources of volunteers, managing volunteer enquiries and addressing feedback to ensure a seamless, supportive volunteer experience.</li><li>Develop and implement strategic outreach programmes and activities to recruit new volunteers, raise awareness, and expand the charity’s volunteer network, ensuring alignment with the charity's mission and operational goals.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements: -</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma in social work or its equivalent.</li><li>Experience in the social service sector will be an advantage.</li><li>Strong inter-personal skills and ability to manage and motivate a pool of volunteers.</li></ul>",
